The Director, corps mobilization of National Youths Service Corps (NYSC) Headquarters, Mrs Nnenna Ukonu, has urged corps members currently in orientation camp at Umunya, Anambra state NYSC temporary site to imbibe the entrepreneurial spirit of the people of the state. She said the spirit will assist them to become employers of labour after their service year. The director who was on a visit to the state NYSC camp also challenged corps members not to lobby to be relocated out of their posted areas. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE The director also cautioned corps members against incessant and unauthorized journeys while serving, urging them to stop unnecessary  trips  to avoid inherent dangers like accident and others. She said, instead of making unnecessary journey, “avail yourselves of the different information technologies to reach out to your parents and loved ones”. She equally reminded them to use the opportunity offered by the NYSC skills acquisition programme to upgrade themselves towards self-reliance at the end of their service year. Earlier, the state NYSC coordinator, Mr Kehinde Aremu, said a total of 2,220 corps members were deployed to the state, adding that 1,080 were males while 1,140 were females. Aremu described the corps members conduct in the state as satisfactorily and also thanked the NYSC Director for the visit. Be agents of change, NYSC boss tells corps members NYSC bans unauthorized journeys by corps members NYSC’s Skill acquisition programme produces successful entrepreneurs –DG Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin